{ In a combination, you normally only use active moves: checks, captures, various attacking moves or threats. In this lesson, it is precisely these active possibilities on which you should be concentrating. Special attention needs to be paid to the first moves.  A. Alekhine – V. Mikenas, Kemeri 1937   In the game, Black played:  1...Bxe4?!  And obtained just a small advantage.  Instead Black could have played the combination... }
1... Rc2 2. Qxc2 Qxf3+ 3. Kg1 Bh3 4. Nf6+ Nxf6 { Winning immediately. } *


