{ Kofman – Kotlerman, Ukrainian Ch 1947  White has a strong attack. }
1. Qg6+ Kf8 2. Re6 { An important, active, attacking move which his opponent cannot ignore. } 2... Qc5 { 2...Bxe6  3.dxe6  leads to a situation in which Black can do nothing about the threat of mate on  f7. } 3. Rxf6+ { A typical sacrifice which opens up the king's position. } 3... exf6 4. Qxf6+ Kg8 { Or  4...Ke8  5.Qxh8++–. } 5. Qg6+ Kf8 6. Ne6+ { And White wins: } 6... Ke7 7. Qf6+ Kd6 { Or  7...Ke8  8.Ng7#. } 8. Nf4+ Be6 9. Qxe6# { 1-0 White wins by checkmate. } *


